    <h2 class="mb2"><img src="/en/7fl296000001yg1i-img/obirin_top_v13_r8_c8.gif" width="422" height="23" alt="About the University"></h2>
    <p class="txt">J. F. Oberlin University is a private four-year university located in Machida, a suburb of Tokyo. Founded in 1946 by Reverend Yasuzo Shimizu, the university is comprised of a College of Arts and Sciences and three professional colleges, as well as a graduate division. With an enrollment of nearly 9,000 students, many of them from overseas, J. F. Oberlin University seeks to foster global citizens on the basis of Christian values.<br> </p> 
